<p>As you can see from the table above, most of my machines run OpenBSD. Some dualboot OpenBSD and Windows XP (for games or when I must use MSIE (but see <a href="girotel/">this</a> - one reason less to boot Windows)). My Cobalt RaQ3 is not supported by OpenBSD, so I chose my preferred Linux distribution, Debian, for it. Debian also runs on my XBox (not listed above). <s>The gateway still runs Slackware, I want to move this job to alfalfa, but I first must decide what to do about my mail.</s>
